      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">42.709-3</ph> Responsibilities.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2521e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                   The
cognizant contracting officer is responsible for-</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2521e27" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                         Determining
whether the penalties in <xref href="FAR-i1075370.dita#i1075370"
                              base="i1075370"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">42.709-2</xref>(a)
should be assessed;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2521e39" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                         Determining
whether such penalties should be waived pursuant to <xref href="FAR-i1075430.dita#i1075430"
                              base="i1075430"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">42.709-6</xref>; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2521e51" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                         Referring
the matter to the appropriate criminal investigative organization
for review and for appropriate coordination of remedies, if there
is evidence that the contractor knowingly submitted unallowable
costs.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d2521e62" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                   The contract
auditor, in the review and/or the determination of final indirect
cost proposals for contracts subject to this section, is responsible
for-</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2521e72" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                         Recommending
to the contracting officer which costs may be unallowable and subject
to the penalties in <xref href="FAR-i1075370.dita#i1075370"
                              base="i1075370"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">42.709-2</xref>(a);</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2521e84" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                         Providing
rationale and supporting documentation for any recommendation; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d2521e93" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                         Referring
the matter to the appropriate criminal investigative organization
for review and for appropriate coordination of remedies, if there
is evidence that the contractor knowingly submitted unallowable
costs.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
